Must install...
1. Latest Python Version 
Make sure to check the option to "Add Python to PATH" during installation.

2. Install Required Libraries:
You'll need three libraries for your code:

pip (helps with installs)
requests (for making HTTP requests)
pyttsx3 (for text-to-speech)
json (comes with Python, so no need to install it separately)
To install the necessary libraries, run the following command in your terminal/command prompt:
pip install requests pyttsx3

3. setup ollama API locally
For this to work, you need to have the Ollama service running locally at http://localhost:11434

For speach to speach you will need to also install...

Speech_recognition (pip install SpeechRecognition)
PyAudio (pip install pyaudio)

With the final script the wakeword will be hey ai, to end the chat the phrase is end chat and to kill the script the word is kill. 
